.Dd April 19, 2026
.Dt PROWLD.CONF 5
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm prowld.conf
.Nd prowld daemon configuration file
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Pa prowld.conf
file contains global configuration settings for the
.Xr prowld 8
service management daemon.
It is parsed by
.Xr libucl 3
and accepts UCL or JSON syntax.
.Pp
The file is typically located at
.Pa /etc/prowld/prowld.conf .
It must be owned by root and must not be world-writable;
otherwise
.Xr prowld 8
will ignore it and log a warning.
.Sh SCHEMA
The following keys are recognised at the top level of the configuration:
.Bl -tag -width "max_concurrent_starts"
.It Va max_concurrent_starts
Maximum number of jobs that may be simultaneously transitioning to the
.Cm starting
state.
Accepts an integer greater than or equal to zero, or the string
.Dq auto .
Zero and
.Dq auto
both select the default of
.Va ncpu * 2 ,
with a minimum of 4.
This limits parallelism during the initial startup wave and subsequent
dependency triggers, preventing resource exhaustion.
.It Va shutdown_timeout
System-wide budget in seconds for an orderly shutdown.
During a graceful stop,
.Xr prowld 8
waits for services marked with
.Va shutdown_wait: true
to exit, up to this total limit.
Default: 300.
.It Va debug
Boolean.
If true, enables verbose logging to standard error in addition to
.Xr syslog 3 .
The command-line
.Fl d
flag always takes precedence over this setting.
Default: false.
.El
.Sh FILES
.Bl -tag -width "/etc/prowld/prowld.conf" -compact
.It Pa /etc/prowld/prowld.conf
The default configuration file path.
.It Pa /etc/prowld/prowld.conf.sample
A sample configuration file showing default values.
.El
.Sh EXAMPLES
A typical configuration using UCL syntax:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
max_concurrent_starts = auto
shutdown_timeout = 120
debug = false
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr libucl 3 ,
.Xr prowld 8 ,
.Xr prowl-unit 5
.Sh HISTORY
.Nm
first appeared in MidnightBSD 4.1.
